---
import LocationLayout from '../../../layouts/LocationLayout.astro';
import FAQSection from '../../../components/FAQSection.astro';
import locations from '../../../data/locations.json';
import pricing from '../../../data/pricing.json';
import services from '../../../data/services.json';

const loc = locations.locations[1];
const p = pricing.services.hullCleaning;

const faqs = [
  { q: "Is Torquay's fouling different from Brixham?", a: "Yes. Torquay Marina sits on a more open stretch of coastline than Brixham's enclosed harbour, so the water is generally clearer with lower nutrient levels. Fouling at Torquay tends to be lighter but still consistent — expect soft algae and biofilm growth throughout summer, with barnacle settlement peaking in July and August." },
  { q: "Can you clean GRP (fibreglass) hulls at Torquay without damage?", a: "Absolutely. Most yachts at Torquay Marina are GRP construction, and our Keelcrab Pro is specifically designed for this. We use soft nylon brush heads that are A.N.C.C.P. certified not to damage antifouling coatings or the gel coat beneath. The robot's controlled pressure is far gentler than manual scrubbing or pressure washing." },
  { q: "Do motor yachts need cleaning more or less often than sailing yachts?", a: "Motor yachts generally benefit from more frequent cleaning because their flatter, wider hull surfaces present a larger target for fouling and they're more sensitive to drag. A fouled planing hull can lose significant top-end speed and increase fuel consumption dramatically. We typically recommend 4–6 cleans per year for motor cruisers at Torquay." },
];
---
<LocationLayout
  title="Hull Cleaning in Torquay"
  description="Premium robotic hull cleaning at Torquay Marina, the English Riviera's 5 Gold Anchor facility. Vessels up to 30m. HD video report included. From £15/metre."
  locationName={loc.name} locationSlug={loc.slug} marina={loc.marina} tagline="Premium Hull Cleaning at Torquay Marina"
  berths={loc.berths} maxVesselLength={loc.maxVesselLength} access={loc.access}
  foulingFactors={loc.foulingFactors} contentAngle={loc.contentAngle}
  heroImage="/images/locations/torquay-marina.png"
  breadcrumbService="Hull Cleaning" breadcrumbServiceSlug="hull-cleaning"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>A 5 Gold Anchor Marina Deserves 5 Gold Anchor Hull Care</h2>
          <p>Torquay Marina has earned its 5 Gold Anchor rating through relentless investment in facilities, services, and the overall customer experience. But even in a world-class marina, what's happening beneath the waterline is invisible to anyone walking the pontoons — and neglected hulls don't discriminate by postcode.</p>
          <p>Torquay's position on the English Riviera means warmer sea temperatures than much of the UK coastline. That warmth drives stronger seasonal fouling, particularly from June through September when barnacle larvae are most active. Vessels berthed here year-round will typically see faster growth rates than those in colder northern marinas, making regular professional cleaning essential for maintaining fuel efficiency and hull longevity.</p>

          <h3>Why Torquay's Larger Vessels Need Specialist Attention</h3>
          <p>Torquay Marina accommodates vessels up to 30 metres — substantially larger than most South Devon marinas can handle. Cleaning a 25-metre motor yacht is a fundamentally different operation to cleaning a 30-foot sailing yacht. The underwater surface area increases exponentially with length, and the hull geometry of larger vessels demands a systematic approach that manual diver cleaning rarely delivers consistently.</p>
          <p>Our Keelcrab Pro excels in exactly these conditions. The robot maintains constant brush pressure regardless of hull size, moves methodically across the surface at a consistent speed, and delivers the same quality of clean on metre twenty-five as it does on metre one. For owners of larger vessels, this consistency is the key differentiator — and the HD video we provide afterwards proves it.</p>

          <h3>The Torquay Visitor Effect</h3>
          <p>Torquay Marina attracts a high volume of visiting yachts during summer, particularly during regatta weekends. This transient traffic introduces biological material from other harbours — including, potentially, invasive non-native species. Keeping your hull clean contributes to the biosecurity of the marina ecosystem, a concern Dart Harbour has been particularly vocal about in recent years.</p>
          <p>For charter fleet operators and sailing schools, a clean hull directly impacts business performance. A fouled vessel underperforms, burns more fuel, and creates a poor first impression. Regular cleaning ensures every vessel in your fleet is ready to perform when clients step aboard.</p>

          <h3>Practical Details for Torquay Boat Owners</h3>
          <p>Torquay Marina offers 24/7 access via the lock gates, giving us more scheduling flexibility than the half-tide access at Brixham. We can typically accommodate same-week bookings during the quieter months and aim for 7-10 days during peak summer season. Your boat stays in the water throughout — we operate from the pontoon alongside your vessel, and the entire process is completed without you needing to be present.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="price-box">
            <span class="price-box__label">Hull Cleaning</span>
            <span class="price-box__amount">£{p.pricePerMetre}</span>
            <span class="price-box__unit">per metre</span>
            <span class="price-box__min">Min: £{p.minimumCharge}</span>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary" style="width:100%;margin-top:var(--space-md)">Book a Clean</a>
          </div>
          <div class="sidebar-info">
            <h4>Torquay-Specific Notes</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>24/7 lock gate access — flexible scheduling</li>
              <li>Vessels up to 30m accommodated</li>
              <li>Warmer English Riviera waters = faster fouling</li>
              <li>High visitor traffic — biosecurity matters</li>
              <li>Same-week bookings often available off-peak</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="other-services">
            <h4>Also in Torquay</h4>
            <a href="/locations/torquay/hull-inspection">Hull Inspection →</a>
            <a href="/locations/torquay/maintenance-plans">Maintenance Plans →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section__header">
        <h2>Why Clean Your Hull?</h2>
        <p class="section__subtitle">The real, measurable benefits of professional robotic hull cleaning — backed by industry research and IMO guidelines.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid--3">
        {services.services[0].benefits.map((benefit) => (
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">{benefit.title}</h3>
            <p class="card__text">{benefit.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section__header">
        <h2>Who Benefits Most from Hull Cleaning in Torquay?</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid--3">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card__icon">🏆</div>
          <h3 class="card__title">Performance-Focused Sailors</h3>
          <p class="card__text">If you race out of Torquay, even light biofilm costs you boat speed. Our pre-race clean removes growth down to bare antifoul, giving you the best possible waterline for competitive sailing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card__icon">🚤</div>
          <h3 class="card__title">Motor Yacht Owners</h3>
          <p class="card__text">Larger motor vessels burn more fuel than any other boat type — and a fouled hull amplifies that cost exponentially. Regular cleaning on a 20m+ vessel can save hundreds in diesel over a season.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card__icon">📋</div>
          <h3 class="card__title">Charter Fleet Operators</h3>
          <p class="card__text">Client expectations are high at a 5 Gold Anchor marina. A "clean and check" before every charter departure ensures your vessels are presentable, performing, and documented.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- FAQs -->
  <FAQSection faqs={faqs} />

</LocationLayout>

<style>
  .content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-3xl); align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .content-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .content-main p { color: var(--text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: 1.8; }
  .content-main h3 { margin-top: var(--space-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-md); font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .price-box { background: var(--surface); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); position: sticky; top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-lg)); }
  .price-box__label { display: block; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); }
  .price-box__amount { display: block; font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); }
  .price-box__unit { display: block; color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .price-box__min { display: block; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.8rem; margin-top: var(--space-xs); }
  .sidebar-info { background: var(--surface); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); }
  .sidebar-info h4 { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  .sidebar-info ul { list-style: none; }
  .sidebar-info li { padding: var(--space-xs) 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-light); }
  .sidebar-info li::before { content: '→ '; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
  .other-services { background: var(--surface); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); }
  .other-services h4 { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  .other-services a { display: block; padding: var(--space-sm) 0; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; }
</style>
